Thirteen Saftu affiliates are briefing the media about a letter served to general secretary Zwelinzima Vavi intending to place him on precautionary suspension. Vavi states the decision to suspend him is illegal and unconstitutional, deliberately vague and politically motivated. JOHANNESBURG -Â Saftu-affiliated unions are holding a briefing about the move to place general secretary Zwelinzima Vavi on precautionary suspension. Vavi is being investigated for alleged financial and administrative violations. Saftu says the investigation will also include allegations that Vavi disrespected or undermined constitutional structures and resolutions.